ğŸ§  Why Change the Nonce?
In Bitcoin mining, miners are trying to find a hash of the block that starts with a certain number of leading zeroes (based on difficulty).

The hash output is unpredictable â€” even changing 1 tiny part (like the nonce) gives a completely different hash. So miners must keep changing the nonce and hashing again until they get lucky.

ğŸ” Visualizing Nonce Attempts
Letâ€™s assume this is your block content:

